HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1004
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Faye Strong Watson
upon her induction into the Clay County Sports
Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly pay tribute to those gifted athletes,
coaches, and administrators who have attained the very pinnacle of sporting achievement; and
WHEREAS, Faye Strong Watson is one such legendary three-sport athlete, who was
recently inducted into the Clay County Sports Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, an iconic figure within the community, Ms. Watson enjoyed one of the
longest careers in local sports history, either playing or coaching for nearly six decades from
1960 to 2018; and
WHEREAS, Faye Strong Watson's historic athletic career began on a dirt basketball
court at Moss Elementary School, continued at Celina High School on the hardwood, kept
rolling on the softball diamond, and culminated with an impressive tennis career; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Watson was the leading scorer on a Moss basketball team that
defeated Celina in elementary school, before the two teams came together at Celina High
School to form one of the best squads the legendary John Teeples ever coached; and
WHEREAS, before graduating in 1965, Faye Strong Watson was a three-year letterman
in basketball and a part-time starter during her senior year, playing with four future Clay County
Hall of Fame members; and
WHEREAS, after playing slow-pitch softball for many years, Ms. Watson became the
first-ever Celina High School fast-pitch softball coach; starting the program in 1986, she expertly
coached and mentored her players, and they soon bonded together to become the best team in
the area; and
HJR1004
