- 1 -

WHEREAS, her Lady Dawgs finished as district runners-up in 1987, won the district
championship in 1988, and claimed both the district championship and the region championship
in 1989 to advance to the sub-state round, an accomplishment that still stands unequalled in
Celina softball history; and
WHEREAS, Faye Strong Watson was also a dominant tennis player who won over 300
matches over the course of four decades (1978-2018), playing in leagues and tournaments all
across Tennessee and Kentucky; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Watson excelled as a singles player, but she also played doubles and
mixed doubles; among her many titles, she won the UTSA-sanctioned forties-age-class
tournament and the UTSA regional doubles state championship and played in the national
region championship; and
WHEREAS, Faye Strong Watson demonstrated leadership, skill, and versatility
throughout her long and prolific athletic career, and it is fitting that we should honor her on this
special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Faye Strong Watson upon her induction into
the Clay County Sports Hall of Fame and extend to her our best wishes for much continued
success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
